summary: You know what I’d love to have in Captain Marvel, another cameo (or even more) of SHIELD director Peggy Carter, she’d be in the...
body:
You know what I’d love to have in Captain Marvel, another cameo (or even more) of SHIELD director Peggy Carter, she’d be in the seventies, so surely she wouldn’t have retired yet. 

I’d also love Carol’s adrenaline junkie thing of flying to the edge of space, letting herself free fall, and absorbing the friction burn.

title: 27 September 2018 (#635)
body:
Last night I again found myself going into the reaction video black hole on YouTube. This time around it was for people reacting to the new Captain Marvel trailer. 

I loved the trailer but there are so many other people that was not so into the trailer. This I just could not understand. So I decided to see peoples reaction to the trailer. What I figured out it is because it is clear that people who did not like the trailer are mostly people who don’t care for the character. Then there are people like me who don’t know the character but are so excited to finally see a female lead Marvel movie. DC already showed them with Wonder Woman that it is something we all need.

As I was going through the reaction videos, I stumbled across one specific video of someone who absolutely loves the character. The video from Miss Faye Reacts actually had me in tears. There is just something so pure to see fans finally getting the movie they always wanted. This naturally just makes me want to learn more about the character and I will definitely start with Miss Faye’s tumblr @themightycaptainmarvel.

summary: No. Fucking NO. Carol Danvers may have been part of Mar-Vel's story, but she was introduced in 68, but he was introduced in...
question: No. Fucking NO. Carol Danvers may have been part of Mar-Vel's story, but she was introduced in 68, but he was introduced in fucking 67, and she didn't become Ms Marvel till 77. TEN FUCKING YEARS LATER. I know you don't know much about comics so you have to take people at their word but sweet fucking Jesus. Also, Monica became Captain Marvel about when Carol became Binary back in 82, after Carol had lost her powers to Rogue. These things do not fucking overlap.
answer:
I see.

I think that I’m going to have to temporarily ban asks about Captain Marvel until the film comes out and people start behaving terribly.

summary: This week Valerie, Angela and Tatiana tackle all things Disney, which of course includes Star Wars and Marvel. First, we deal...
caption:
This week Valerie, Angela and Tatiana tackle all things Disney, which of course includes Star Wars and Marvel. First, we deal with the Ralph Breaks the Internet and the restoration of Princess Tiana’s skin tone (0:30), then we talk about Star Wars slowing down (5:20). Kevin Feige will be taking charge of X-Men and Fantastic Four (15:00), which of course leads us to Avengers 4 spoilers and theories (20:00). Next up is assorted Disney and Marvel news, including the fact that Chloe Zhao will be directing the Eternals movie (30:00). Finally, we gush about the Captain Marvel trailer for the rest of the podcast (42:20).

Let us know your thoughts in the comments below, or check out our Podomatic page here.
